08/04/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A National Operational Group for Combatting Terrorism began work in Sarajevo on Thursday (April 7th).
Security Minister Sadik Ahmetovic told a press conference it represents "a start of the fight against terrorism at an institutional level", adding that 19 police agencies and institutions will be represented.
"Terrorism has no religion or nationality.
We want to assume an active part in European and global security," Ahmetovic said.
The group has been supported by the German and US governments.
(SRNA, Dnevni Avaz, Radio Free Europe - 07/04/11)
